- How do you roll back a faulty policy update?

## Why This Is Asked
Demonstrates practical API boundary design, basic rate limiting, and graceful degradation in a beginner-friendly Azure setup.

## Key Concepts
- API Management quotas and rate limits by user
- Per-user spend cap and simple state store
- Fallback to rule-based replies on failure
- Observability for quotas and failures

## Code Example
```javascript
// Minimal mock of request flow with quota check and fallback
async function handle(req) {
  const user = req.userId;
  const quota = getUserQuota(user);
  if (quota.remaining <= 0) return cannedReply();
  try {
    const res = await callOpenAI(req.payload);
    debitQuota(user, req.payload.length);
    return res;
  } catch {
    return cannedReply();
  }
}
```

## Follow-up Questions
- How would you test quota expiry and fallback paths?
- How would you simulate OpenAI downtime in a local test environment?
